```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bean & Brew</title>
    <style>
    *{margin:0, padding:0} body{background:bg-gray-900, font-size:14px, line-height:10, padding:0, margin:0} nav{display:flex, justify-content:center, bg-off-4, padding:10px, margin:0} nav a{text-decoration:underline, padding:0, color:gray-900, hover:color=gray-900} section{text-align:center, padding:0, margin:0} h1{font-size:bold, padding:0, margin:0} button{bg-off-4, padding:0, margin:0} form{display:grid, padding:0, margin:0} input{type=text, padding:0, margin:0} input[type=email]{padding:0, margin:0} input[type=submit]{padding:0, margin:0}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<nav>
<a href="#">Home</a>  -   <a href="#">Menu</a>  -   <a href="#">Contact</a>
</nav>
<section>
<h1>Bean & Brew</h1>
<p>Fresh roasted coffee, bre & brew.</p>
<button id="order">Order Now</button>
</section>
<form action="/submit" id="contactForm">
<input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required>
<input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email address" required>
<input type="submit" value="Send">
</form>
<script>
document.getElementById('order').addEventListener('click', function () { alert('Thank for your order!') })
document.getElementById('contactForm').addEventListener('submit', function (event => e. preventDefault, alert('Conf of your order'))
</script>
</body>
</html>
```
